post_text:
Message from the Superintendent: "We are all saddened to learn of the passing of Werner Schmidt. We are extremely grateful for all his generous donations to the Dennis-Yarmouth Regional School District over the years and especially the donation of the Observatory and other equipment used by our Astronomy program. We were fortunate to be able to celebrate Werner’s 100th birthday with him at the Observatory! He will surely be missed by all of us! Our condolences to his family and our thanks to them for sharing him with us all these years!!"

Carol Woodbury, Dennis-Yarmouth Superintendent

https://www.capecodtimes.com/obituaries/20200614/werner-h-schmidt-105

post_text:
Message From the Superintendent 3/18/20
Dear DY Families,

When I send these emails I am using the emergency contact feature to share this information with as many people as possible. I am sorry if I fill up your inbox and you don’t need this information, however, in difficult times I believe such information can be helpful to everyone.

Attached you will find information about the Yarmouth Food Pantry and a list of websites that might be helpful to parents with children. The last link on the information page is for MyTelemedicine in case you need it.

Thank you for staying out of public places. I have noticed that the parks are no longer full. We hope this will make a difference.

We are working on plans to help our students continue learning. As soon as they are ready I will be in touch.

Best wishes,

Carol Woodbury, Superintendent

Families who qualify can get affordable internet access through Comcast. According to their website:

As the country deals with the effects of the Coronavirus (COVID-19), Comcast is taking immediate steps to help connect more low-income families to the Internet at home. Effective Monday, March 16, 2020, new Internet Essentials customers will receive two free months of Internet service. We are also increasing the speed of the program to 25 Mbps downloads, and 3 Mbps uploads for all new and existing customers.

After your first two free months expire, you can either cancel the service (which you can do at any time) or keep it as a regular paying Internet Essentials customer. You will receive an easy to use self-install-kit that includes a cable modem (to receive service at your home) with a WiFi router (to connect your devices without wires). There is no term contract or credit check and no shipping fee for equipment.Click the link for details.

https://www.internetessentials.com/covid19

A message from DENNIS YARMOUTH REGIONAL SD

Good Afternoon,

When I sent out the message on Friday about closing school this week I felt we needed some additional planning time to determine if an extended closure was needed. After a review over the weekend and putting our food service program in place, so our students will be able to get food during this closure, I feel confident that closing for two weeks is the prudent thing to do.

Therefore, Dennis-Yarmouth Regional School District will be closed for the next two weeks (March 16-March 29). The information that I have right now is indicating that the closure could go on much longer. I will continue to update you as soon as more information is available.

No one should come into the schools on Monday, March 16 except for those who have already been directed to do so. I ask that both staff and families check your email for updates.

Stay well, DY! Go Dolphins!

Carol A. Woodbury, Superintendent

· Close public spaces and cancel gatherings/events

· Do not meet people at playgrounds, or use play dates, parties and sleepovers to keep students busy when schools are closed

· Take care of yourself and your family while maintaining social distance

· Reduce the frequency of trips to the stores and restaurants

· If you are sick, isolate yourself and contact medical professionals

post_text:
A message to Wixon Families from Mr. Blake:

Good morning Wixon Families. This is Tim Blake, principal at Wixon. This morning we had a smoke alarm go off at the school. Police and fire departments are still here investigating the reason the alarm went off. Currently all students are inside safe and warm in the cafeteria and auditorium. Please do not come to the school to pick up your children, all students are safe and warm inside. We ask for your patience and please do not come to the school to pick up your children, they are inside safe and warm. The kids have been really well behaved during this time.

Sincerely,

Timothy Blake

Principal

Nathaniel H. Wixon School

post_text:
10th grade students will take MCAS on ipads this year. If your ipad is in need of repair, please turn it in right away so we can get you a loaner and get your ipad out for repair and back in time for the real MCAS. If you can't find your ipad, please let us know immediately.

There will be an infrastructure trial on Feb. 25th for all 10th grade students to take a practice test on their ipads, kind of like a dress rehearsal for the real thing. We expect all students to have their ipads charged and ready to be used that morning. We will have a few loaners available that day, but you need to make sure you make every effort to bring yours charged with you that day.
